𝐏𝐥𝐚𝐲𝐰𝐫𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐓𝐲𝐩𝐞 𝐒𝐜𝐫𝐢𝐩𝐭:

It’s a Framework for Web Automation. It enables reliable end to end testing for modern Web Applications

Key Features of Playwright:

1. 𝑼𝒏𝒊𝒇𝒊𝒆𝒅 𝑨𝑷𝑰:   Playwright works across all modern browser engines (Chromium, WebKit, Firefox) using Unified API

2. 𝑯𝒆𝒂𝒅𝒍𝒆𝒔𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝑯𝒆𝒂𝒅𝒆𝒅: Supports Headless and UI Mod Execution

3. 𝑹𝒆𝒔𝒊𝒍𝒊𝒆𝒏𝒕 𝑻𝒆𝒔𝒕𝒊𝒏𝒈: Due to Auto Waits and Auto Retry, Test cases Flakiness is eleminated

4. 𝑬𝒂𝒔𝒚 𝑫𝒆𝒃𝒖𝒈𝒈𝒊𝒏𝒈: It offers features like stack trace, video recording which makes debugging easy

5. 𝑬𝒂𝒔𝒚 𝑺𝒆𝒕 𝒖𝒑: Setting up Playwright is just a few clicks

6. 𝑭𝒂𝒔𝒕: As It directly talks to Browser Engines using CDP and Custom protocols, It Makes execution fast


𝐇𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐨𝐫𝐲 𝐨𝐟 𝐏𝐥𝐚𝐲𝐰𝐫𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭: 

•Playwright was Released on 31st January 2020 by Microsoft
•Playwright was created by Engineers who developed Puppeteer at Google
•Limitations of Puppeteer: 
Limited Cross browser support, Only chromium support, limited multiple browser context handling
•Limitation of Selenium:
Slower, Flakiness, Parallel Execution

•Why Playwright was created?

To Overcomes Limitation of above tools and to create a solution Fast Like Pupeteer, Cross browser, Isolation, Auto wait, Unified API 𝑻𝒉𝒊𝒔 𝒊𝒔 𝒘𝒉𝒆𝒓𝒆 𝑷𝒍𝒂𝒚𝒘𝒓𝒊𝒈𝒉𝒕 𝑩𝒐𝒓𝒏

